						<summary>

						<p>Slab near the Āñjaneya temple (northern wall) (in Nagari Script).</p>						

						<p><hi rend="bold">15th century A.D.</hi></p>						

						<p>The record is very badly damaged and mutilated. It opens with an invocatory passage to the god Gaṇēśa followed by the verse Namastunga etc. The rest is illegible.</p>						

						<p>It is in characters of the 15th century A.D.</p>						

